Mix apple juice, sage and onion in 3 1/2 to 5-quart slow cooker. Season roast with salt and pepper. Add roast with salt and pepper, turning to coat with liquid. Cover and cook on High 5 to 6 hours or on Low 8 to 9 hours until meat is tender. During the last half hour of cooking, stir in the apples. To serve, slice roast and serve with the apples, onions and pan juices.